#: ../../source/Changelog.rst:507
msgid "Version 1.14.1 - May 5, 2026"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Changelog.rst:509
msgid ""
"Incremental fixes on top of the v1.14.0 PCM scaffold. Adds a non-cyclic "
"hydro mode and battery SOC carryover. Multi-window rolling now solves on "
"scenarios without binding min-outflow on cascaded hydro -- the cross-"
"window cascade-state issue moves to v1.15+."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Changelog.rst:518
msgid ""
"New ``cyclic_hydro`` param flag (default ``True`` for CEM compatibility)."
" When ``False`` (set automatically by "
"``prepshot.pcm._build_window_params``), ``hydro.inflow_rule`` drops the "
"upstream-cascade contribution at hours where ``h - delay < hour[0]`` -- "
"instead of wrapping modularly into the same window. This makes each PCM "
"window stand alone in time, rather than implicitly looping its end into "
"its beginning."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Changelog.rst:525
msgid ""
"Battery SOC carryover in ``prepshot.pcm._extract_window_state``: read "
"each ``model.storage[terminal_hour, m, y, z, te]`` (in MWh), divide by "
"``cap_existing[y,z,te] * energy_to_power_ratio[te] * dt`` to recover the "
"per-unit-of-cap fraction that ``initial_energy_storage_level`` expects, "
"clamp to ``[0, 1]``, and pass into the next window's params. Storage "
"techs with zero capacity are skipped (the next window's lookup defaults "
"to 0)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Changelog.rst:536
msgid ""
"**Cascading hydro across windows**: at window boundaries, downstream "
"stations see only their natural (incremental) inflow because the "
"upstream's outflow during the lookback period lives in the previous "
"window's solve and isn't carried forward. When downstream "
"``reservoir_outflow_min > natural_inflow``, water balance drains storage "
"below ``storage_min`` and the sub-problem is infeasible. Workaround: run "
"``--horizon == --step == period_length`` (single-window). Permanent fix "
"in v1.15+ via a cross-window cascade-state vector."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Changelog.rst:545
msgid ""
"**Annual carbon cap not rescaled to window length**: the naive filter "
"applies the full-year cap to each window. Not binding for the shipped "
"examples but wrong on principle; will rescale by ``window_hours / "
"hours_in_year`` in v1.15."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Changelog.rst:551
msgid "Version 1.14.0 - May 5, 2026"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Changelog.rst:553
msgid ""
"New mode: **production-cost-model (PCM)** with a rolling-horizon driver. "
"Companion to the default capacity-expansion (CEM) flow in ``run.py``: PCM"
" takes a fixed fleet (from a prior CEM ``baseline.nc`` or a user-supplied"
" capacity CSV) and solves *only* hourly dispatch over a chosen year, in "
"windows. PowNet- and PyPSA-style."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Changelog.rst:559
msgid ""
"This is the **Phase A scaffold** of the PCM-fidelity roadmap (Phase B = "
"unit commitment overlay, Phase C = DC flow which already landed in "
"v1.13). It's shipped as **alpha** -- single-window mode works end-to-end;"
" multi-window rolling has a known cyclic-wrap interaction documented in "
"the module docstring and tracked for v1.14.1."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Changelog.rst:568
msgid "``prepshot/pcm.py`` -- new module + CLI entry point::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Changelog.rst:573
msgid ""
"Supports both ``.nc`` (CEM result) and ``.csv`` capacity sources. Output "
"lands in ``output/baseline_pcm.nc`` so it doesn't collide with CEM's "
"``baseline.nc``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Changelog.rst:577
msgid ""
"New ``skip_end_storage`` param flag plumbed through "
"``hydro.end_storage_rule`` and ``storage.end_energy_storage_rule``; when "
"``True``, the cyclical \"terminal storage = initial storage\" equality is"
" dropped so PCM windows can have free terminal SOC (carried into the next"
" window)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Changelog.rst:583
msgid ""
"``prepshot.load_data.extract_config_data`` now also returns "
"``hours_in_year`` so PCM windows can recompute the cost-objective "
"``weight`` for shorter time slices."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Changelog.rst:590
msgid ""
"``model.hour_p`` now derives from ``hour[0]`` (``[hour[0] - 1] + hour``) "
"instead of being hardcoded to ``[0] + hour``. CEM behaviour is unchanged "
"because CEM uses ``hour=[1..N]``; PCM windows starting at ``hour[0] > 1``"
" get the correct prior-hour anchor for storage balances."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Changelog.rst:596
msgid ""
"``storage.init_energy_storage_rule`` and "
"``storage.end_energy_storage_rule`` reference ``model.hour_p[0]`` instead"
" of literal ``0`` for the prior-hour storage variable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Changelog.rst:600
msgid ""
"``generation.ramping_up_rule`` / ``ramping_down_rule`` skip the inter-"
"hour delta when ``h == model.hour[0]`` (no ``h - 1`` in the set). Was ``1"
" < h``, now ``h > model.hour[0]``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Changelog.rst:604
msgid ""
"``hydro.inflow_rule`` rewrites the cyclic-wrap arithmetic to use modular "
"indexing relative to ``hour[0]``, ``hour[-1]`` instead of the implicit "
"``[1..24]`` assumption. CEM behaviour is mathematically identical for "
"``hour=[1..N]``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Changelog.rst:610
msgid "Known limitations (v1.14.0 alpha)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Changelog.rst:612
msgid ""
"**Multi-window rolling is unstable.** The hydro module's cyclic "
"``inflow_rule`` couples ``upstream.outflow[hour[-1]]`` to "
"``downstream.inflow[hour[0]]`` within each window; with carry-over state "
"at ``hour[0]-1``, the second window's cyclic loop can have no feasible "
"point. Workaround: run with ``--horizon == --step == period_length`` "
"(single-window PCM = fixed-capacity CEM dispatch). v1.14.1 will switch "
"hydro to a non-cyclic rolling form."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Changelog.rst:620
msgid ""
"**Battery state carryover deferred.** ``initial_energy_storage_ level`` "
"is per-unit-of-cap, not absolute MWh; an absolute-MWh state extracted "
"from a solved window doesn't compose with that convention. Each window "
"currently re-initialises batteries to the dataset's default SOC. Fix in "
"v1.14.1."
msgstr ""

