#: ../../source/Changelog.rst:1423
msgid "Why long-format"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Changelog.rst:1425
msgid ""
"Adding a dimension to a long-format file is a non-breaking column add, "
"not a reshape. This eliminates the recurring \"the bound files were "
"reshaped from (tech, zone) to (zone, tech, year)\" class of breakage, "
"which historically required migrating every existing input directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Changelog.rst:1430
msgid ""
"Long-format is the canonical input shape used by OSeMOSYS, GenX, Switch, "
"and PyPSA -- researchers familiar with those tools will find the "
"convention intuitive."
msgstr ""

