msgid ""
"``prepshot/load_data.py::read_long_csv`` -- new reader for tidy CSVs. "
"Convention: dimension columns first, value column last. Output dict shape"
" matches what the wide-format reader produces for the same parameter "
"(scalar keys for 1 dim, tuple keys for 2+ dims), so model code is "
"unchanged regardless of which format is on disk."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Changelog.rst:1442
msgid ""
"``params.json`` entries support a new ``\"format\": \"long\"`` key. When "
"set, the loader looks for ``<file_name>.csv`` instead of "
"``<file_name>.xlsx``, and skips the wide-format-specific keys "
"(``index_cols``, ``header_rows``, ``unstack_levels``, "
"``first_col_only``)."
msgstr ""

